{"parse":{"title":"phone","pageid":34113,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"{{also|phoné|-phone|'phone}}\n==English==\n{{wp}}\n[[Image:Dialog gr 1972.jpg|thumb|right|A rotary-dial phone]]\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈfəʊ̯n/|a=RP}}\n** {{audio|en|en-uk-phone.ogg|a=UK}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈfoʊ̯n/|/ˈfɔʊ̯n/|a=GA,CA}}\n** {{audio|en|en-us-phone.ogg|a=US}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈfəʉn/|/ˈfɐ̝ʉn/|a=AU}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈfon/|a=Scotland}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈfoːn/|a=Wales,non-toe-tow}}\n* {{rhymes|en|əʊn|s=1}}\n* {{hyph|en|phone}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\n{{etymon|en|id=device|telephone<id:device>|tree=1}}\n{{clipping|en|telephone}}; {{etydate|1884|nocap=1}}.\n\n====Alternative forms====\n* {{alter|en|'phone||dated}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# A [[device]] for [[transmit]]ting [[conversation]]s and other sounds in [[real time]] across [[distance]]s, now often a small portable unit also capable of running [[software]] etc.\n#: {{hypo|en|cell phone|speakerphone|clamshell phone|flip phone|mobile phone|smartphone}}\n#: {{ux|en|Daragh's on the '''phone''' at the moment. He'll call you when he's finished.}}\n#: {{ux|en|My '''phone''' ran out of battery.}}\n#: {{ux|en|There's an old-fashioned '''phone''' in the doctor's waiting room - it doesn't work anymore, of course.}}\n# {{lb|en|colloquial}} A person's [[telephone number]] (as a means of contact); [[digits]].\n#* '''1994''', Warren G feat. Nate Dogg ''{{w|Regulate (song)|Regulate}}'' (song)\n#*: It was a clear black night, a clear white moon / Warren G was on the streets tryin' to consume / Some skirts for the eve so I can get some '''phones''' / Rollin' in my ride, chillin' all alone\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|en|phoneaholic|softphone|pass the phone\n|answer phone\n|bag phone\n|bar phone| basic phone|phone case\n|bat phone,bat-phone\n|brick phone\n|burn phone\n|burner phone|portable phone\n|buzzer phone\n|camera phone\n|can I use your phone\n|candy bar phone\n|car phone\n|car-phone\n|cell phone lot\n|cell-phone\n|cellular phone\n|cordless phone\n|door phone\n|entry phone\n|entry-phone\n|feature phone\n|flip-phone\n|have more chins than a Chinese phone book\n|hold the phone\n|home phone\n|house phone\n|Jesus phone\n|Obama phone\n|on the phone|phone-free\n|pay phone\n|phone bank\n|phone book\n|phone booth|airphone|batphone|cameraphone|camphone|cardphone|carphone|computerphone|cryptophone|dataphone|deskphone|diaphone|diphone|doorphone|dumbphone|earphone|entryphone|eyephone|featurephone|freephone|Googlephone|handphone|headphone|housephone|interphone|iPhone|isophone|keyphone|miniphone|multiphone|netphone|payphone|phablet|phlog|phlogging|phonable|phonebook|phonebox|phonecam|phonecard|phoneful|phonelike|phonemaker|phonemark|phoneography|phonepost|phoneward|phonewise|phoneword|phreak|phreaking|phub|picturephone|pocketphone|polyphone|satphone|screenphone|superphone|symphonious|textphone|touchphone|trackerphone|trimphone|triphone|ultraphone|videophone|viewphone|visionphone|visiphone|watchphone|webphone|wristphone\n|phone box\n|phone call\n|phone card\n|phone hacking\n|phone home\n|phone jack\n|phone line\n|phone monkey\n|phone number\n|phone survey\n|phone zombie\n|phone-in\n|phone-in show\n|phone-out\n|phoneputer\n|phone-sex\n|pick up the phone\n|rotary phone\n|satellite phone\n|slide phone\n|slider phone\n|smart phone\n|stick phone\n|swivel phone\n|touch phone\n|touch-phone\n|trap phone\n|what is your phone number\n|what's your phone number\n|world phone\n|phonecall\n|banana phone\n|candlestick phone\n|money phone\n|phone jail\n|phone tree\n|wireless phone\n|phoneless\n|phone sex\n|phone tag\n|phonicate\n|pornophone\n|speakerphone\n}}\n\n=====Descendants=====\n* {{desc|my|ဖုန်း|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|inc-hnd|-|bor=1}}\n** {{desc|hi|फ़ोन}}\n** {{desc|ur|فون|tr=fon}}\n* {{desc|ga|fón|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|fa|bor=1}}\n** {{desc|prs|فون|tr=fōn}}\n* {{desc|pt|fone|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ta|ஃபோன்|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|vi|phôn|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|cy|ffôn|bor=1}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-see|telephone}}\n\n=====See also=====\n* {{l|en|Thesaurus:phone}}\n\n====Verb====\n{{en-verb}}\n\n# {{lb|en|ambitransitive}} To [[call]] (someone) using a [[telephone]].\n#: {{syn|en|call|phone up|ring|telephone}}\n#: {{ux|en|'''Phone''' me as soon as you land at the airport.}}\n#: {{ux|en|Her father told her to '''phone''' him to pick her up in case it started raining heavily.}}\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=1934|author=Ernest Bramah|title=The Bravo of London\n|passage=\"You bloody fools!\" shrieked Nickle, stung by a sudden dreadful inspiration, \"we've let him '''phone'''. He has got through!\"}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2010|author=Tyler Keevil|chapter=32|title=Fireball|location=Cardigan, Ceredigion|publisher=[[w:Parthian Books|Parthian]]|page=148|pageurl=https://archive.org/details/fireballbrightyo00tyle/page/148/mode/1up|isbn=978-1-906998-10-3|passage=It wasn’t like he was dying to get it off his chest. I think he only '''phoned''' because he knew how excited I’d be to hear about it.}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|en|title=Terms derived from ''phone'' (etymology 1—verb)\n|phone ahead|phone home\n|phone in\n|phone up|unphoned\n}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top|to call (someone) on the telephone}}\n* Afrikaans: {{t|af|telefoneer}}\n* Albanian: {{t+|sq|telefonoj}}\n* Arabic: {{t|ar|تَلْفَنَ}} ({{lang|und|sc=Arab|[[ل|لـِ]]}} ''li-'')\n* Aramaic:\n*: Assyrian Neo-Aramaic: {{t|aii|ܚܘܼܛܵܡܲܠܸܠ|tr=ḳuṭamālil}}, {{t|aii|ܡܲܚܒܸܪ|tr=māḳbir}}\n* Armenian: {{t+|hy|զանգել}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{t|az|zəng etmək}}, {{t|az|zəng vurmaq}}\n* Basque: {{t|eu|telefonatu}}, {{t|eu|telefonoz deitu}}\n* Belarusian: {{t|be|звані́ць|impf}}, {{t|be|пазвані́ць|pf}}; {{t|be|тэлефанава́ць|impf}}, {{t|be|патэлефанава́ць|pf}}\n* Bengali: {{t|bn|ফোন করা}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|телефони́рам|impf|pf}}, {{t+|bg|обаждам|impf|alt=оба́ждам се}}, {{t+|bg|обадя|pf|alt=оба́дя се}}\n* Burmese: {{t|my|[[ဖုန်း]][[ဆက်]]}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|telefonar}}, {{t+|ca|trucar}}\n* Chamorro: {{t|ch|dengua'}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|打電話|tr=dǎ diànhuà}}\n* Czech: {{t+|cs|telefonovat|impf}}, {{t|cs|zatelefonovat|pf}}, {{t+|cs|volat|impf}}, {{t+|cs|zavolat|pf}}\n* Danish: {{t+|da|ringe}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|telefoneren}}, {{t+|nl|opbellen}}\n* Esperanto: {{t+|eo|telefoni}}\n* Estonian: {{t+|et|helistama}}\n* Faroese: {{t|fo|ringja}}\n* Finnish: {{t|fi|[[soittaa]] (puhelimella)}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|téléphoner}}, {{t+|fr|appeler}}, {{t+|fr|phoner}}\n* German: {{t+|de|anrufen}}, {{t+|de|telefonieren}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|τηλεφωνώ}}, {{t|el|[[παίρνω]] [[τηλέφωνο]]}}, {{q|colloquial}}: {{t+|el|παίρνω}}, {{t+|el|καλώ}}\n* Guarani:\n*: Paraguayan Guarani: {{t-check|gug|mopumbyry}}\n* Hebrew: {{t+|he|צלצל|tr=tsiltsél|alt=צילצל \\ צִלְצֵל}}\n* Hindi: {{t|hi|फ़ोन करना}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|telefonál}}\n* Icelandic: {{t+|is|hringja}}\n* Ido: {{t+|io|telefonar}}\n* Indonesian: {{t+|id|telepon}}\n* Interlingua: {{t|ia|telephonar}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|telefonare}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|電話をかける|tr=でんわをかける, denwa o kakeru}}, {{t+|ja|電話|tr=でんわする, denwa suru|alt=電話する}}\n* Khmer: {{t+|km|ទូរសព្ទ}}\n* Korean: {{t|ko|전화를 걸다}}, {{t+|ko|전화하다}}\n* Lao: {{t+|lo|ໂທລະສັບ}}\n* Latvian: {{t|lv|telefonēt}}, {{t|lv|zvanīt}}, {{t|lv|piezvanīt}}\n* Lithuanian: {{t|lt|skambinti}}\n* Luganda: {{t|lg|essimu}}\n* Luxembourgish: {{t|lb|telefonéieren}}, {{t|lb|uruffen}}\n* Macedonian: {{t|mk|телефони́ра|impf|pf}}, {{t|mk|ѕвони|impf}}, {{t|mk|заѕвони|pf}}\n* Persian:\n*: Dari: {{t|fa|تیلفون کردن|tr=têlifôn kardan}}, {{t|fa|تیلفون زدن|tr=têlifôn zadan}}, {{t+|fa|زنگ زدن|tr=zang zadan}}\n*: Iranian Persian: {{t|fa|دورواژیدن|tr=durvâžidan}}, {{t+|fa|تلفن کردن|tr=telefon kardan}}, {{t+|fa|تلفن زدن|tr=telefon zadan}}, {{t+|fa|زنگ زدن|tr=zang zadan}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|dzwonić|impf}}, {{t+|pl|zadzwonić|pf}}, {{t+|pl|telefonować|impf}}, {{t+|pl|zatelefonować|pf}}\n* Portuguese: {{t|pt|[[telefonar]] [[para]]}}, {{t+|pt|chamar}}, {{t|pt|[[ligar]] [[para]]}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|telefona|alt=a telefona}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|звони́ть|impf}}, {{t+|ru|позвони́ть|pf}} (по [[телефон|телефону]] po telefónu), {{t+|ru|телефони́ровать|impf}} {{g|pf}} {{qualifier|rare}}\n* Sanskrit: {{t|sa|दूरवाणी}}, {{t|sa|दूरवाणीं करोति}}\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{t|gd|fòn}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t|sh|телефони́рати|impf|pf}}\n*: Latin: {{t+|sh|telefonírati|impf|pf}}\n* Sindhi: {{t|sd|ڏُور وائڻُ|tr=Ddoor Vaainn}}\n* Slovak: {{t|sk|telefonovať|impf}}, {{t|sk|zatelefonovať|pf}}, {{t|sk|volať|impf}}, {{t|sk|zavolať|pf}}\n* Slovene: {{t|sl|telefonirati|impf|pf}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|telefonear}}, {{t|es|llamar por teléfono}}, {{t+|es|timbrar}} {{qualifier|America}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|ringa}}, {{t+|sv|telefonera}}\n* Tagalog: {{t|tl|tumawag}}, {{t|tl|tawagan}}, {{t|tl|tumelepono}}\n* Tajik: {{t|tg|телефон кардан}}\n* Tamil: {{t|ta|ஃபோன் பண்ணு}}\n* Thai: {{t+|th|โทร|tr=too}}, {{t+|th|โทรศัพท์}}\n* Tibetan: {{t|bo|ཁ་དཔར་གཏོང་བ}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|aramak}}, {{t+|tr|telefon etmek}}, {{t+|tr|telefonlamak}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t|uk|дзвони́ти|impf}}, {{t|uk|подзвони́ти|pf}}, {{t+|uk|телефонува́ти|impf}}, {{t|uk|зателефонува́ти|pf}}\n* Urdu: {{t|ur|فون کرنا|tr=fon karnā}}, {{t|ur|ملانا|tr=milānā}}\n* Uzbek: {{t|uz|telefon qilmoq}}, {{t|uz|qoʻngʻiroq qilmoq}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t|vi|gọi điện thoại}}, {{t|vi|gọi điện}}, {{t|vi|kêu điện thoại}}, {{t+|vi|điện thoại}}, {{t+|vi|điện}}\n* Welsh: {{t+|cy|ffonio}}\n* Yiddish: {{t|yi|טעלעפֿאָנירן}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n{{root|en|ine-pro|*bʰeh₂-|id=speak}}\nFrom {{der|en|grc|φωνή|t=sound}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# {{lb|en|phonetics}} A speech segment that possesses distinct physical or perceptual properties, considered as a physical event without regard to its place in the phonology of a language.\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|en|phonal}}\n\n=====Related terms=====\n{{col|en\n|phonetic\n|phonetically\n|phonetics\n|phonology\n|phoneme\n}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top|speech segment}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|звук|m}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|fon|m}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|語音|tr=yǔyīn}}\n* Czech: {{t+|cs|hláska|f}}, {{t+|cs|fón}}\n* Danish: {{t|da|sproglyd|c}}\n* Estonian: {{t|et|häälik}}, {{t|et|foon}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|äänne}}, {{t+|fi|fooni}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|phone|m}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Phon|n}}\n* Hungarian: {{t|hu|fón}}, {{t|hu|hangszegmentum}}\n* Indonesian: {{t+|id|fon}}\n* Irish: {{t|ga|foghar|m}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|fono|m}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|音価|tr=おんか, onka}}, {{t+|ja|単音|tr=たんおん, tan'on}}\n* Persian: {{t|fa|دورگویال}}, {{t+|fa|آوا|tr=âvâ}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|głoska|f}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|fone|m}}\n* Russian: {{t|ru|фо́на|f}}, {{t+|ru|фоне́ма|f}}\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{t|gd|foghar|m}}\n* Sicilian: {{t|scn|fonu|m}}\n* Slovak: {{t+|sk|hláska|f}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|fono|m}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|fon|c}}\n* Urdu: {{t|ur|صوت|m|tr=saut}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=ehnop|nepho-|pheno-|pheon}}\n\n==French==\n{{wp|fr:}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{fr-IPA}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-WikiLucas00-phone.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Lyon>>)}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{root|fr|ine-pro|*bʰeh₂-|id=speak}}\n{{fr-noun|m}}\n\n# [[phon]] (a unit of apparent loudness)\n# {{lb|fr|linguistics}} {{l|en|phone}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|fr|verb form}}\n\n# {{inflection of|fr|phoner||1//3|s|pres|ind//sub|;|2|s|impr}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:fr:TLFi}}\n\n{{C|fr|Acoustics}}"}}